<HEAD>Stocks Close At Record High, Dollar Weakens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> stock market closed at a record high Tuesday while the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar weakened. In the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average closed at 27,246.77, 33.32 points higher than on Monday. The market's main barometer briefly reached the all time high of 27,339.14 shortly after Tuesday's opening, but profit-taking thwarted the early morning rally, traders said. Meanwhile, the dollar closed at 124.57 yen, 0.43 yen lower than Monday's close of 125. It opened at 124.65 yen and traded in a narrow range of 124.55 yen to 124.70 yen, traders said. Analysts said initial bullish sentiment in the stock market following the record close on Monday pushed stock prices up in early trading, but the trend slowly reversed, fueled by profit-taking. `` The market started out on a bullish note, but then ran out of gas and started moving down,'' said a trader at a major securities firm, who asked not to be identified.
