<BYLINE>By GEORGE TIBBITS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman accused of killing her husband and another person discussed killing him with drug overdoses months before he died from cyanide-tainted aspirin, her daughter testified at the product-tampering trial. <PERSON> Cindy </PERSON> <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON>, 28, told a federal court jury Monday that a `` discontented'' <PERSON> Stella </PERSON> <PERSON> Nickell </PERSON> briefly mentioned divorcing <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Nickell </PERSON> but `` she said she was not going to lose half of everything she had fought so hard to get. `` Based on what my mother had told me prior to my dad's death, I believed that she did it,'' Ms. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> said in a packed <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Court courtroom. Her testimony was to continue today in the trial, now in its second week. On Monday, Ms. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> said her mother had questioned her about such drugs as heroin, cocaine and amphetamines; where they could be obtained and how much would cause an overdose. Assistant <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Joanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Maida </PERSON> asked Ms. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> whether her mother ever discussed specific people in the conversations. `` My dad, <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Nickell </PERSON>,'' she replied, referring to her stepfather. Prosecutors say Mrs. <PERSON> Nickell </PERSON>, the first person in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to be tried on charges of causing death by tampering with over-the-counter capsules, plotted to kill <PERSON> Nickell </PERSON> to collect insurance. But prosecutors said the plot unraveled when Ms. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> challenged her mother's attempt to make his June 1986 death and that of <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Katherine </PERSON> <PERSON> Snow </PERSON> a few weeks later look like random murders. Prosecutors have suggested there were no links between the victims other than the way they died. Government inv