<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rock star <PERSON> Madonna </PERSON>'s 18-year-old brother has pleaded innocent to charges that he injured a police officer checking out loud noises at a downtown home. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Ciccone </PERSON> allegedly `` shoved, or slammed, or shut, or kicked without warning the door in the officer's face, knocking him down, breaking his glasses and cutting his forehead,'' Police Chief <PERSON> Theodore </PERSON> <PERSON> Glynn </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Ciccone </PERSON>, youngest of <PERSON> Madonna </PERSON>'s seven brothers and sisters and listed in court documents as living with his parents in the northern <LOCATION> Detroit </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Rochester </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>, pleaded innocent Monday to a charge of resisting and obstructing a police officer. District Court Judge <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Shipper </PERSON> released him on personal bond pending a preliminary examination May 5. The misdemeanor charge carries a maximum penalty of two years in prison. Police officer <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Weidner </PERSON>, 31, and another police officer went to the house April 16 when they heard what sounded like shots or firecrackers, according to <PERSON> Glynn </PERSON> and police reports. They found a loud party in progress and were asking questions at the door when `` Mr. <PERSON> Ciccone </PERSON> kicked it from the other side into <PERSON> Weidner </PERSON>'s face,'' the police report said. <PERSON> Weidner </PERSON> sustainted a cut that required more than 30 stitches and has not returned to full duty, officials said.
