's troops on Villa's activities in the <LOCATION> Piedras </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Negras </LOCATION> area, <PERSON> Armistad </PERSON> said. After her husband died in 1937, Mrs. <PERSON> Chavez </PERSON> moved to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to work in restaurants in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> INS </ORGANIZATION> said. Usually, amnesty applicants must wait six years before receiving an application for citizenship, but officials speeded up the process for Mrs. <PERSON> Escobedo </PERSON>. <PERSON> Armistad </PERSON> said he expects the same will be done for Mrs. <PERSON> Chavez </PERSON>. Mrs. <PERSON> Chavez </PERSON> is the mother of 12 children and has 55 grandchildren, 112 great-grandchildren and four great-great-grandchildren. She lives with a daughter in this <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> town.
