<HEAD>Bodies of Five Men Found In Trunk Of Parked Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The bullet-riddled bodies of five young men were found Tuesday in the trunk of a car parked at a suburban <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Juan </LOCATION> housing project, police said. Each victim's hands and feet were tied and each had been shot repeatedly, police said. The men apparently were slain elsewhere, put into car's trunk and driven to the <LOCATION> Sabana </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bajo </LOCATION> housing project in the suburb of <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, police spokesman <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Santiago </PERSON> said. The bodies were taken to the <ORGANIZATION> Forensic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sciences </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> at the <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Piedras </LOCATION> for examination. Institute director <PERSON> Pio </PERSON> <PERSON> Rechani </PERSON> said all were between the age of 18 and 23. One of the victims was identified as <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> <PERSON> Alberto </PERSON> <PERSON> Diaz </PERSON> <PERSON> Orta </PERSON>, 20, of the Ramon T. Colon Housing Project in <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>. The identities of the others were not known.
