</TEXT>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 After a lawmaker declared it was time for all Floridians to receive their `` just desserts,'' the state <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> voted Tuesday to designate key lime pie as the official state pie. The legislation was sent to the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> on a vote of 107-3. `` We have been deprived too long,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Norman </PERSON> <PERSON> Ostrau </PERSON>, who sponsored the bill. `` From sea to shining sea, we are saying ` Let there be key lime pie.''' The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> appeared to be on a roll for designating state symbols. On Monday, the chamber approved a bill to designate <LOCATION> Myakka </LOCATION> fine sand as the official state soil. One of the three House members who voted against the key lime pie bill said he had had enough. `` It's getting absurd,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Dale </PERSON> <PERSON> Patchett </PERSON>, who also voted against the <LOCATION> Myakka </LOCATION> fine sand bill. `` It cost $ 500 or $ 600 to move -LRB- this bill -RRB- through the House. Besides, I do n't like key lime pie.'' The pies can be made from the juice of any variety of the tart citrus fruit, but some proponents say the only real ones are those made with the small, greenish-yellow variety known as the key lime. Eggs and sweetened, condensed milk are the other primary ingredients.
