<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> and independent oil exporters are gathering for a series of meetings aimed at tightening oil supplies and boosting prices. Officials of the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> Exporting Countries and rival oil producers expressed cautious optimism Monday that an agreement could be reached this week on joint measures to support prices. `` Any meeting between <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> and non-OPEC -LRB- nations -RRB- is important, but this one is particularly so because prices seem to be weak,'' said <LOCATION> Indonesian </LOCATION> delegate <PERSON> Subroto </PERSON>, the nation's former oil minister.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sales of domestically-produced cars and light trucks have risen slightly in mid-April from the same period last year, according to automakers. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday its daily sales rate rose 21.4 percent during the April 11-20 period, while <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> reported a 4.4 percent decline and <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> was off 2.6 percent. Sales of all domestically made cars and light trucks totaled 353,314 for the eight-day period, up from 308,240 in the nine-day period a year earlier.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sales of existing homes edged up 2.5 percent in March for the second month in a row, a real estate trade group says. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Realtors </ORGANIZATION> said Monday that existing single-family homes sold at a seasonally adjusted rate of 3.33 million units last month. The March rise matched a 2.5 percent increase in February, but the sales rate remained 9.8 percent below March 1987.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> J.P. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stevens </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to be acquired for $ 1.22 billion by <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Point-Pepperell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which plans to split the textile giant's assets with a partner and a rival bidder. <LOCATION> Pepperell </LOCATION>, which made its bid in conjunction with <ORGANIZATION> NTC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, said Monday it will pay $ 68.50 in cash for each of <PERSON> Stevens </PERSON> 17.8 million outstanding shares under terms of deal forged over the weekend. <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Point </LOCATION>, Ga.-based <ORGANIZATION> Pepperell </ORGANIZATION> will sell $ 530 million in <LOCATION> Stevens </LOCATION> assets to the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Odyssey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, its rival in the lengthy takeover battle.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three health groups are asking the government to begin regulating low-tar cigarettes on grounds that advertising claims for the products make them a drug subject to federal oversight. If accepted by the <ORGANIZATION> Food </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drug </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, agreed to by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and upheld in court, the arguments made by the three groups on Monday would place the <ORGANIZATION> FDA </ORGANIZATION> in the ironic position of regulating cigarettes low in tar and nicotine, but not other cigarettes.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> has let stand an <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> telephone company's ban on sexually explicit dial-up message services. In the first `` dial-a-porn'' case to reach the high court, the justices without comment declined Monday to hear arguments that <ORGANIZATION> Mountain </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>'s refusal to carry sexually explicit message services violates free-speech rights. The court's action came a week after <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> sent to President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> a bill that would ban all dial-a-porn services, which are available to callers through `` 976'' exchanges and <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T's `` 900'' long-distance lines.
