<HEAD>Cartier To Acquire Controlling Interest In Piaget, Baume &amp; Mercier</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday it will acquire a controlling interest in Swiss watchmakers <ORGANIZATION> Piaget </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Mercier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION>, a move that will give the French luxury products company a commanding share of the upscale watch market. Terms of the transaction were not disclosed, but <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Alain </PERSON> <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> said the acquisition should help boost <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION>'s sales to $ 840 million this year. <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Mercier </PERSON> had combined sales of $ 162 million last year. <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> also said the acquisition will give <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> control of more than 40 percent of the $ 2.2 billion international luxury watch market, and the combined company should pose a formidable challenge to upscale watchmaker <PERSON> Rolex </PERSON>. The two companies will be held through <ORGANIZATION> Piaget </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Mercier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holding </ORGANIZATION>, a parent company that will be 75 percent owned by <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> and 25 percent owned by <PERSON> Luxco </PERSON>, a Luxembourg-based holding company that <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> and its partners control. The holding company will hold 60 percent of both <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Mercier </PERSON>, and the <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> family will retain the remaining interest in each company. Both <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Mercier </PERSON>, which are owned by the <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> family, will retain their management `` at least for the time being,'' <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> said. The move follows a wave of mergers and acquisitions in the international luxury goods business, with further consolidation likely in the watchmaking industry. <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> disclosed <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> hopes within the next year to gain a controlling interest in <ORGANIZATION> Ebel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION>, another Swiss watchmaker. He also said discussions are underway with two other privately-owned European luxury goods companies with a view to expanding <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION>'s market share in other product lines, but he declined to give details. In addition to watches, <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> is known for its jewelry, cigarette lighters, luxury leather goods and perfumes. <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> is 46.8 percent owned by <ORGANIZATION> Rothmans </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Sofina </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S.A. </ORGANIZATION>, a unit of the <ORGANIZATION> Societe </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Generale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> de </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Belgique </ORGANIZATION> group of <LOCATION> Belgium </LOCATION>, and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> brokerage firm <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> hold up to 18 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> would not identify other <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> shareholders. <PERSON> Cartier </PERSON>'s consolidated sales jumped by 36.8 percent last year to $ 680 million from $ 497 million in 1986, while aggregate sales of <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Baume </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Mercier </PERSON> were up 15 percent to $ 161.9 million. <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION> has never disclosed its earnings, but <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> said the company's sales could reach $ 840 million this year. <PERSON> Piaget </PERSON>, which initiated the takeover talks with <ORGANIZATION> Cartier </ORGANIZATION>, holds the No. 1 position for luxury watch sales in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> despite a sales slump that hit the sector in 1986, <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> said.
