<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreetClosing     04-26 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0166</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market posted some modest gains today, although it gave back some of the morning's advance during afternoon trading. The market gained strength through most of the morning, but retreated in the early afternoon before advancing once again in the final hour. Trading was relatively light. Before the market opened, the government reported that the the economy grew at a 2.3 percent annual rate in the first three months of 1988. That was down from growth of 4.8 percent in the October-December quarter, but the growth estimate fell well within most forecasts. Analysts said the market has taken some encouragement from the fact that the economy has not bogged down as some had feared after last October's crash. But they noted that many individual investors remain leery about getting back into the market because of the volatility that has followed the crash.
</TEXT>
