der will stand at least until May 13, when the court is scheduled to hear the BNS appeal. <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> also asked the <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> court to order BNS to extend its bid indefinitely. The offer, which has been extended weekly, is set to expire at midnight Friday, unless extended again. Some analysts said the number of shares tendered, combined with apparent lack of progress by <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION>' board in developing a competing plan, could force <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> to negotiate with BNS. <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Drahuschak </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Butcher </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Singer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> might have to reconsider its opposition to the bid if the shares tendered reach 65 percent to 70 percent by the end of the week. Without approval from <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION>' board, BNS would have to get 85 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION>' shares for its bid to be successful under provisions of the anti-takeover law in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION>, where <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> is incorporated.
