<HEAD>Lucky Stores Considers Alternative Takeover Proposals</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Lucky </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which three weeks ago rejected a $ 1.74 billion takeover bid that would have created the nation's largest supermarket chain, said Tuesday it has received other takeover proposals. Lucky, <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>'s second-biggest grocery chain, said it was reviewing the new bids as well as other possibilities that would benefit shareholders more than <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s pending tender offer of $ 45 a share. A spokeswoman for Lucky declined to elaborate on the brief formal statement. The company's soaring stock, which was trading at $ 32 a share a month ago before <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> announced its offer, closed up another $ 1.37 -LCB- to $ 55.37 -LCB- Tuesday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. In a separate development, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> _ which has extended the deadline on its offer to Saturday _ suggested to the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> that Lucky hold an auction among interested parties. Industry analysts said they had only vague ideas as to the identity of Lucky's new suitors but said the company would be an attractive acquisition. `` It's -LRB- one of -RRB- the largest in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> with a very strong identity of being the low-price leader and it has a meaningful position in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. And it's a well-run company,'' said <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Rotter </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Morgan </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Olmstead </PERSON>, <ORGANIZAT